      "text": [
        " اَلْإِحْرَامِ قَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ إِنَّمَا يُكْرَهُ اَلْحَرِيرُ اَلْمُبْهَمُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2636 - Abu Basir al-Muradi asked Imam (as) about a woman wearing qazz (a fabric made from silk and other materials) while in Ihram.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it. What is disliked is pure silk (al-harir al-mubham).\""
        ]
      }
    },
